Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Push Buttons
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0000mrl
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 8 Oct 2018
Push Buttons: Laurie Taylor explores the pleasure, panic and the politics of pushing. The touch of a finger can summon a taxi, turn on a TV, call for an elevator or 'like' a Facebook post. But are buttons simply neutral and natural mechanisms which ease our daily lives? He's joined by Rachel Plotnick, Assistant Professor of Cinema and Media Studies at Indiana University, Steven Connor, Professor of English at the University of Cambridge and Barbara Speed, the opinion editor at the i newspaper. Producer: Jayne Egerton Show less